4 §58.10. Battle of New Orleans Day
5 A. A day shall be designated to commemorate the stunning victory by
6 American forces consisting of United States army regulars, marines, and sailors, area
7 militia, and Battalions of Free Men of Color, Baratarian privateers, Attakapas
8 Dragoons, volunteers from Tennessee, Kentucky, and Mississippi (Hinds' Dragoons),
9 Choctaws, and individuals who were formerly Spanish subjects and French citizens
10 who fought for their new country under the command of Major General Andrew
11 Jackson against the invading British forces on the plains of Chalmette in the last
12 major military engagement between the United States and Great Britain in the War
13 of 1812.
14 B. The eighth day of January is hereby designated as the Battle of New
15 Orleans Day throughout the state of Louisiana to honor those who served in this
16 historic battle. The governor or local governing authorities may declare the Battle
17 of New Orleans Day a holiday.
