HB 61 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Bayham
Abstract: Provides for the Battle of New Orleans Day.
Present law provides for days of public rest and legal holidays including George
Washington's Birthday and Presidents' Day.
Proposed law retains present law with regard to Washington's Birthday but deletes all
references to Presidents' Day.
Proposed law designates Jan. 8th as the Battle of New Orleans Day to honor those who
served in this historic battle where American forces represented by volunteers from
numerous military backgrounds scored a stunning victory over Great Britain in the War of
1812.
Proposed law permits the governor or local governing authority to declare the Battle of New
Orleans a holiday.
