Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Judiciary to the original
bill:
1. Delete references to Presidents' Day as a day of public rest and legal holiday.
2. Specify the volunteers and other militia that assisted the U.S. in its victory over
Great Britain in the War of 1812.
3. Permit the governor or local governing authority to declare the Battle of New
Orleans Day a holiday.
